str2: Therefore, then. Apparently a primary word; certainly, or accordingly.

str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
Indisputable, undeniable, not to be contradicted. Indisputable.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Nominative Neuter Singular
str2: Third person singular active present of deo; also deon deh-on'; neuter active participle of the same; both used impersonally; it is Necessary.
To begin, am, exist, be in possession. From hupo and archomai; to begin under, i.e. Come into existence; expletively, to exist (verb).

parse: Verb - Perfect Participle Middle or Passive - Accusative Masculine Plural
str2: To let down, lower; I keep down, restrain, pacify. From kata and stello; to put down, i.e. Quell.
To do, perform, accomplish; be in any condition, i.e. I fare; I exact, require.
Impulsive, rash, reckless. From a compound of pro and pipto; falling forward, i.e. Headlong.
